#### Function Fingerprint Computation (Lines 24-71)
Computes a stable SHA-256 hash of:
- **Source text** (verbatim, including whitespace)
- **Parameter names and types** (sorted for determinism)
- **Branch structure** (ID, line, condition text, type – sorted by ID)

```rust
pub fn compute_function_fingerprint(source_text: &str, analysis: &FunctionAnalysis) -> String {
    let mut hasher = Sha256::new();

    // Hash source text
    hasher.update(b"source:");
    hasher.update(source_text.as_bytes());

    // Hash parameters (sorted by name)
    let mut params: Vec<_> = analysis.params.iter()...collect();
    params.sort();
    hasher.update(b"params:");
    for p in &params { ... }

    // Hash branch structure (sorted by ID)
    let mut branches: Vec<_> = analysis.branches.iter()...collect();
    branches.sort();
    hasher.update(b"branches:");
    for b in &branches { ... }

    format!("{:x}", hasher.finalize())
}
```

#### Deep Fingerprints (Lines 81-101)
Incorporates **callee deep fingerprints** to detect transitive changes:
- A caller becomes stale if any of its in-scope callees change
- Processed leaves-first (ensures callee fingerprints are available)

```rust
pub fn compute_deep_fingerprint(
    shallow_fingerprint: &str,
    callee_deep_fingerprints: &HashMap<String, String>,
    callees: &HashSet<String>,
) -> String {
    let mut hasher = Sha256::new();
    hasher.update(b"shallow:");
    hasher.update(shallow_fingerprint.as_bytes());

    // Hash in-scope callee deep fingerprints (sorted by name)
    let mut callee_fps: Vec<_> = callees.iter()
        .filter_map(|c| callee_deep_fingerprints.get(c).map(|fp| (c.as_str(), fp.as_str())))
        .collect();
    callee_fps.sort_by_key(|(name, _)| *name);

    hasher.update(b"callees:");
    for (name, fp) in &callee_fps {
        hasher.update(name.as_bytes());
        hasher.update(b":");
        hasher.update(fp.as_bytes());
        hasher.update(b"\n");
    }

    format!("{:x}", hasher.finalize())
}
```

